'''Etsy'''是一個美国[[網路商店|網路商店]]平台，以[[手工藝|手工藝]]成品買賣為主要特色，<ref name='NYT-Walker-2007-12-16'>{{cite news | first= Rob | last= Walker | coauthors=  | title= Handmade 2.0 | date= December 16, 2007 | publisher= New York Times | url= http://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/16/magazine/16Crafts-t.html?_r=2&oref=slogin&ref=magazine&pagewanted=all | work= New York Times Magazine | pages=  | accessdate= 2007-12-17 | archive-date= 2012-03-04 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120304170038/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/16/magazine/16Crafts-t.html?_r=2&oref=slogin&ref=magazine&pagewanted=all | dead-url= no }}</ref> ，曾被[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]拿來和[[eBay|eBay]]，[[Amazon|Amazon]]比較，被譽為「祖母的地下室收藏」。<ref name='NYT-Slatalla-2007-1-18'>{{cite news |first= Michelle |last= Slatalla |title= Rooting Around Grandma’s Basement in Cyberspace |date= January 18, 2007 |publisher= New York Times |url= http://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/18/fashion/18Online.html?ex=157680000&en=8b334fa53f7dd9da&ei=5124&partner=permalink&exprod=permalink |accessdate= 2007-12-19 |archive-date= 2012-08-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120808223807/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/18/fashion/18Online.html?ex=157680000&en=8b334fa53f7dd9da&ei=5124&partner=permalink&exprod=permalink |dead-url= no }}</ref>

== 历史 ==

Robert Kalin，Chris Maguire和Haim Schoppik在2005年6月18日成立的Etsy網站，前身是一家稱為iospace的小公司。隨後有Matthew Stinchcomb（[[French_Kicks|French Kicks]]網站成立者）和Jay Nuzzolillo，Simon Forman與Alex Somma加入。投資者則為Union Square Ventures還有[[Flickr|Flickr]]與[[Del.icio.us|Del.icio.us]]的成立者。<ref name='USV-2006-6-5'>{{cite web | author=Fred Wilson | title=Etsy | date=June 5, 2006 | url=http://www.unionsquareventures.com/2006/06/etsy_1.html | accessdate=2007-12-19 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20091005213249/http%3A//www.unionsquareventures.com/2006/06/etsy_1.html | archivedate=2009-10-05 }}</ref>

Etsy網站的搜尋方式有相當多種，可以使用同一色彩來搜尋（透過[[Adobe_Flash|Adobe Flash]]技術<ref name='Techrunch-Arrington-2005-11-8'>{{cite web | first = Michael | last = Arrington | title = Etsy - P2P Commerce with Tagging | publisher = Techcrunch | date = November 8, 2005 | url = http://www.techcrunch.com/2005/11/08/etsy-is-ebay-20/ | accessdate = 2007-12-19 | archive-date = 2008-01-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080101131026/http://www.techcrunch.com/2005/11/08/etsy-is-ebay-20/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>），也可以使用標籤搜尋。

在2007年5月，Etsy網站的銷售達到170萬美元。<ref name='NYT-Ryzik-2007-6-24'>{{cite news | first= Melena | last= Ryzik | title= Where the Crafts Babes and D.I.Y. Dudes Are | date= June 24, 2007 | publisher= New York Times | url= http://www.nytimes.com/2007/06/24/fashion/24renegade.html?_r=2&oref=slogin&ref=style&pagewanted=all&oref=slogin | accessdate= 2007-12-19 | archive-date= 2012-05-06 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120506005714/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/06/24/fashion/24renegade.html?_r=2&oref=slogin&ref=style&pagewanted=all&oref=slogin | dead-url= no }}</ref> 7月29日，Etsy達到一百萬的銷售，並預期在2007年12月中能達成兩百萬美元的銷售。2007年11月，總計Etsy上買家花了四百三十萬美元購買約三十萬項Etsy上刊登的商品，與同年的10月相比，成長了43%。

該站原先預期在2007年6月能開始有利潤，但直到2007年的12月，Etsy都還是一個沒有利潤營收的網站公司。<ref name='IHT-Walker-12-15-07'>{{cite news |1=  |author1= Rob Walker |title= Craft capitalism: Just do it yourself |date= December 15, 2007 |publisher= International Herald Tribune |url= http://www.iht.com/articles/2007/12/14/business/wbcraft.php |accessdate= 2007-12-19 |archive-date= 2009-03-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20090326004915/http://www.iht.com/articles/2007/12/14/business/wbcraft.php |dead-url= no }}</ref>

目前Etsy的營收來自陳列商品手續費，每一件商品收取美金20分，如賣出商品，則收取商品售價3.5%的手續費<ref name='AZcentral-Marion-2006-8-8'>{{cite news | first = Fred | last = Marion | title = Etsy may be the coolest, most feel-good way to shop | date= August 8, 2006 | publisher= Cox News Service | url = http://www.azcentral.com/home/crafty/articles/0808etsy0808.html | accessdate = 2007-12-19 }}</ref>，多數Etsy的商品價格在美金$15到$20元間，而多數的賣家都為女性<ref name='BusinessWeek-6-12-07'>{{cite news | first=Kerry | last=Miller | title=Etsy: A Site for Artisans Takes Off | date=June 12, 2007 | publisher=BusinessWeek | url=http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/jun2007/sb20070611_488723.htm | accessdate=2007-12-19 | archive-date=2007-12-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071211153109/http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/jun2007/sb20070611_488723.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。目前Etsy有一個固定的辦公室在[[紐約市|紐約市]][[布魯克林區|布魯克林區]]。稱為「Etsy Lab」。所有Etsy的公關、促銷和財務等都由此辦公室負責。
2011年9月單月賣出2340萬件商品，目前在一百五十個國家中有一百一十萬名註冊的使用者，並且已經爬升到Alexa全球前兩百大的網站。

2020年4月，Etsy向網站上的所有賣家發出電話，要求他們開始製作口罩來對抗Covid-19。口罩在第三季度約佔商品銷售總額的11％，大約售出2400萬。在 2020 年 COVID-19 大流行期間，Etsy 的股價翻了兩番多。 D.A. Davidson Tom Forte的股票分析師表示，大流行使客戶有動力多次返回網站，而不是通常偶爾購買獨特的產品。<ref name="Etsyhistory">{{Cite web |url=https://www.mg21.com/etsy.html |title=复古创意电商：Etsy, Inc.(ETSY) |publisher=美股之家 |date=2021-06-09 |access-date=2021-06-10 |archive-date=2021-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709131430/https://www.mg21.com/etsy.html }}</ref>。

